title: Metro State Cycling Roadrunner Time Trial
Mesa State College - Mad Cow Classic
description: Road Race and Team Time Trial at Reeder Mesa near Whitewater Colorado.  Criterium in downtown Fruita, Colorado.
course:
Road Race - 29 - 62 miles (depending on category) on the roads of Reeder Mesa.  A couple of steep climbs, sweeping descents and lots of fun.
Team Time Trial - 9 mile gentle climb back up Reader Mesa.  Teams of 3-4 riders.
Criterium - A flat and fast .8 mile course in downtown Fruita including the main circle.
registration: Online registration available through active.com until Thursday March 27th.  On site registration until 30 minutes before race start.
directions:
Road Race - From Denver, Take I-70 West to exit 37 - I-70B  towards Delta / Montrose. At the intersection, turn left onto Highway 50 and continue to Whitewater.  Turn left onto Reader Mesa Road off of Highway 50 at Whitewater.  There is a large dirt parking lot on the right at mile marker 2 on Reader Mesa Road.

Team Time Trial:  Continue on Highway 50 past Whitewater to Kannah Creek  / Land\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'s End Road.  Turn left on Kannah Creek Road and  go approx 2 miles to intersection with Purdy Mesa Road and start of Time Trial.

Criterium: From Denver, take I-70 West to Fruita, turn right off exit and proceed to downtown Fruita and parking.
